# G3X Database Updater

Automatically download and install Garmin aviation databases onto SD cards for G3X Touch flight displays.

## Features

- **Garmin Portal Authentication**: Login to flyGarmin to access your subscribed databases
- **TAW/AWP File Support**: Parse and extract Garmin's proprietary database formats
- **Automatic SD Card Detection**: Find and validate suitable SD cards
- **G3X Directory Structure**: Write files in the exact format expected by G3X Touch
- **Metadata Tracking**: Track installed database versions
- **Systemd Integration**: Trigger automatically when SD cards are inserted

## Background

This project builds upon the excellent work in [jdmtool](https://github.com/dimaryaz/jdmtool), 
particularly the `garmin_login` branch which enables Garmin subscription support. While jdmtool 
focuses on Jeppesen databases and data card programmers, this tool specializes in:

- G3X Touch SD card database installation
- Automatic/unattended operation
- Integration with Raspberry Pi for aircraft-based systems

## Installation

### From PyPI (when published)

```bash
pip install g3x-database-updater
```

### From Source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/g3x-database-updater.git
cd g3x-database-updater
pip install -e .
```

### On Raspberry Pi

```bash
# Install dependencies
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install python3 python3-pip

# Install the package
pip3 install g3x-database-updater

# Install udev rules for auto-detection (optional)
sudo cp systemd/99-g3x-db-sdcard.rules /etc/udev/rules.d/
sudo cp systemd/g3x-db-updater@.service /lib/systemd/system/
sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
```

## Quick Start

### 1. Login to Garmin

```bash
g3x-db-updater login
# Enter your flyGarmin email and password when prompted
```

### 2. List Available Databases

```bash
g3x-db-updater list-databases
```

### 3. Download Databases

```bash
# Download all available databases
g3x-db-updater download all

# Or specific databases by index
g3x-db-updater download 0,1,2
```

### 4. Write to SD Card

```bash
# Scan for SD cards
g3x-db-updater scan-sdcards

# Write TAW files to SD card
g3x-db-updater write downloaded_db.taw
```

### Full Automatic Update

```bash
# Single command for complete update:
g3x-db-updater auto-update
```

## Usage

### Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `login` | Login to Garmin flyGarmin portal |
| `logout` | Clear saved authentication tokens |
| `list-devices` | List registered Garmin devices |
| `list-databases` | List available databases for download |
| `download` | Download database files |
| `extract` | Extract TAW/AWP file contents |
| `scan-sdcards` | Scan for connected SD cards |
| `write` | Write databases to SD card |
| `auto-update` | Full automatic update workflow |

### Login Options

```bash
# Interactive login
g3x-db-updater login

# Login with credentials (for scripts)
g3x-db-updater login -e your@email.com -p yourpassword

# Force re-login
g3x-db-updater login --force
```

### Download Options

```bash
# Download from specific device
g3x-db-updater download -d 0 all

# Download to specific directory
g3x-db-updater download -o /path/to/downloads all
```

### Extract TAW Files

```bash
# List contents without extracting
g3x-db-updater extract --list-only database.taw

# Extract to specific directory
g3x-db-updater extract -o /path/to/output database.taw

# Extract without subdirectory structure
g3x-db-updater extract --flat database.taw
```

### Write to SD Card

```bash
# Auto-detect SD card and write
g3x-db-updater write database.taw

# Write to specific device/mount
g3x-db-updater write -d /dev/sda1 database.taw

# Skip confirmation
g3x-db-updater write -y database.taw
```

## Configuration

Configuration is stored in `~/.g3x_db_updater/`:

```
~/.g3x_db_updater/
├── garmin_tokens.json    # Authentication tokens
├── downloads/            # Downloaded database files
└── config.json          # Optional configuration
```

### Token Storage

Authentication tokens are stored securely with restricted permissions (600). They include:

- Access token for API requests
- Refresh token for session renewal
- Expiration timestamp

### SD Card Requirements

- **Filesystem**: FAT32 (VFAT)
- **Size**: 2GB - 32GB (8GB recommended)
- **Format**: Standard SD or microSD with adapter

## TAW File Format

TAW (Transfer Archive for Windows) files are Garmin's container format for aviation databases.

### Structure

```
TAW File
├── Header
│   ├── Magic bytes (TAW\0 or AWP\0)
│   ├── Version
│   ├── Database type
│   ├── Cycle information
│   └── Metadata strings
└── Regions
    ├── Navigation DB (0x01) -> ldr_sys/avtn_db.bin
    ├── Terrain TDB (0x21) -> terrain.tdb
    ├── Terrain ODB (0x22) -> terrain_9as.odb
    ├── FliteCharts (0x24) -> FCharts.dat
    └── ... other regions
```

### Region Types

| Type | Path | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| 0x01 | ldr_sys/avtn_db.bin | Navigation database |
| 0x10 | safetaxi.bin | SafeTaxi data |
| 0x14 | fc_tpc/fc_tpc.dat | FliteCharts TPC |
| 0x1A | rasters/rasters.xml | Raster data |
| 0x21 | terrain.tdb | Terrain database |
| 0x22 | terrain_9as.odb | Terrain obstacles |
| 0x24 | FCharts.dat | FliteCharts |
| 0x26 | obstacles.odb | Obstacle database |

## G3X SD Card Structure

The tool creates the following directory structure on SD cards:

```
SD Card Root/
├── ldr_sys/
│   └── avtn_db.bin        # Navigation database
├── fc_tpc/
│   └── fc_tpc.dat         # FliteCharts TPC
├── rasters/
│   └── rasters.xml        # Raster data
├── terrain.tdb            # Terrain database
├── terrain_9as.odb        # Terrain obstacles
├── FCharts.dat            # FliteCharts
├── Fcharts.fca            # FliteCharts index
└── .g3x_db_metadata.json  # Version tracking
```

## Systemd Integration

For automatic operation when SD cards are inserted:

### Udev Rule (`99-g3x-db-sdcard.rules`)

```udev
# Trigger on SD card insertion
ACTION=="add", KERNEL=="sd[a-z][0-9]", SUBSYSTEM=="block", \
    ENV{ID_FS_TYPE}=="vfat", \
    TAG+="systemd", ENV{SYSTEMD_WANTS}="g3x-db-updater@%k.service"
```

### Systemd Service (`g3x-db-updater@.service`)

```ini
[Unit]
Description=G3X Database Updater for %i
BindsTo=dev-%i.device
After=dev-%i.device

[Service]
Type=oneshot
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/g3x-db-updater auto-update --device /dev/%i
```

## Integration with G3X Flight Processor

This tool can work alongside the G3X Flight Data Processor. When both are installed:

1. Insert SD card
2. G3X Flight Processor reads flight logs
3. G3X Database Updater checks for/installs database updates
4. Remove SD card

Configure both in `/etc/g3x_processor/config.json`:

```json
{
  "database_updater": {
    "enabled": true,
    "auto_download": true,
    "databases": ["navdata", "terrain", "obstacles"]
  }
}
```

## Troubleshooting

### Authentication Errors

```bash
# Clear tokens and re-login
g3x-db-updater logout
g3x-db-updater login
```

### SD Card Not Detected

```bash
# Check for SD cards manually
lsblk -f

# Mount manually
sudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/sdcard

# Then use explicit path
g3x-db-updater write -d /mnt/sdcard database.taw
```

### TAW Parse Errors

```bash
# List TAW contents to debug
g3x-db-updater extract --list-only problematic.taw
```

### Permission Errors

```bash
# Ensure udev rules are loaded
sudo udevadm control --reload-rules

# Check permissions
ls -la /dev/sda*
```

